Water intervenes as product and reactant in the catabolic reactions (see Eqs. 1–4). However, the concentration of electron donors, ethanol, CO2 and H+ ions are generally very low and catabolic reactions take place within a “dilute aqueous system” [77]. Therefore, the concentration of water is not considered in the calculation of ΔGr0′\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
